Ole Gunnar Solskjaer scored the iconic goal that secured United the treble in 1999. He was asked about Liverpool&rsquo;s long-lost dream this evening, as quoted by the Manchester Evening News:<br />
<br />
&ldquo;Well, for me it was a fantastic final to play in &lsquo;99 and it&rsquo;s always been the last game of the season, a spectacle, you can never ever underrate the FA Cup how much it means and for us it was a big step towards. The semi-final against Arsenal, that was maybe the turning point. The Treble was a fantastic achievement. We hope we&rsquo;re gonna do it again but it&rsquo;s a difficult task and more or less impossible, there are so many good teams around, it has changed domestically, it was either us or Arsenal in &lsquo;99 and now there&rsquo;s more of us.&rdquo;
